,Recommended,297110,18515628,"Posted: 16 October, 2015",all,MPO,"At first, I was disappointed by its limitations.  As I got further into the game, this gave way to more diverse sets of instruments, and you develop the skills to layer music in an enjoyable, more strategic way.  Either way, the game is very entertaining and humorous.  Though levels vary in quality, the game is a great experience if you can get in the zone and make something great - which is helped along by the background music that prompts you with cues.  A terrific introduction to sequencers.The ability to export your songs and give them cool album art is terrific icing on the cake: a permanent way to remember what you did.  Putting a timer on album art creation was also a good way to keep things spontaneous."
