,Recommended,297110,22849296,"Posted: 7 May, 2016",all,Mr.WereWolph,"Here is a list of Pros and Cons of the game.ConsStory line takes less than an hour...This means after you complete the storyline, that's it, everything else you do from then on is not story driven, it's pretty much a studio from that point on. The developers could have stretched out the levels, and made more. But unfortunately there are only 5 levels, including the ""boss battle"". The reason I list this is because there was so much potential in creating bonds between the player and the characters, but just as soon as it happens, the game is over. Also, if you paid for a game that's 3 dollars, wouldn't you want a bit longer experience? That's 5 cents for every minute you play of the storyline.Instrument quality...Some of the instruments sound really wierd and choppy, while others are pretty good, this is a bit bad because free play, from what I have seen (don't quote me on this but I didn't see the feature), is that you cannot choose what instruments to use, they are always randomized, could it inspire interesting sounds and songs? Yeah, but you should def have more control over what you get to use in freeplay.Failure to explain some mechanicsNow this one is questionable, because the main mechanic is making music, and filling the jam meter. But every once in a while, after I finish inserting the notes for a instrument, an explosive like tile floats across the screen to the right, and apparently if you click on it, it explodes or something, idk because the game didn't really tell me.Flashing LightsI noticed that some of the lights in this game were actually a bit intense, not that I am epileptic, but if you are, you may want to consider not playing and I would stamp a warning on this game somewhere if it truely can trigger an epileptic seizure. I guess this one is debatable.Alright, now for the ProsProsEngaging and interesting visuals...You like space? You like dogs? You like interactive backgrounds while you play? I sure do, and I did playing this game.Good music...This is questionable, obviously, as you are the one making the music, but if you know at least a little bit of what you are doing, then the beats will get pretty epic.Exporting your music...Yes, you can actually export your music, I plan on uploading mine to soundcloud because my mixtape is pretty fire, not gonna lie. But yeah, you can get a mp3 file of the song you just made, pretty cool.Innocent and charming atmosphere...Many a times I found myself laughing at how cute and charming the characters were, I guess you could say that they charmed me ''WITH THE POWER OF MUSIC!!!!'But if you really like this game, buy it when it's for sale, so put it in your wishlist, and wait for the next sale, I got it for $0.74, which I feel was worth every penny. Honestly you could buy it for $3 and still feel content."
