,Recommended,297110,15921406,"Posted: 20 May, 2015",all,The Choir Squire,"For such a cheap game, Cosmic DJ really delivers. Even the tutorial had me bopping my head to the beat I created! All you have to do is put different sound effects in at a choice of 4 separate notes. Although 4 isn't much in retrospect, it didn't seem like I had fewer options, rather it seemed like the whole thing was simpler. There's also the added bonus of re-playing the same level many times and making completely different beats each time through. There are several songs you must apply beats to, and at the end of every level it combines all the songs into one *cosmic jam* for you to listen to! The story is light and doesn't get too deep into anything, and always manages to have a little humor sprinkled here and there. This game is perfect for those wanting to have fun with music, and get really creative/funky with it at the same time."
