,Recommended,297110,16028644,"Posted: 27 May, 2015",all,TWD Kenny,"I had tons of fun with this game. Even at full retail price, I'd recommend this game. My only real issue about this game is that it's short- it's VERY short. It only took me 1 hour to finish the story line- which wasn't really much of one. Cosmic DJ is a game where you are a Cosmic DJ and have to save the city from ""Bad Vibes"" from the main antagonist (forgot his name). The antagonist destroys all the ""Jamtennas"" that provide good vibes to the city. As the cosmic DJ, you must fix these ""Jamtennas"" by completing the tasks given. There are 4 Jamtennas you must fix and each Jamtenna offers 4-5 missions where you need to create a song using the tools given and fix the Jamtenna. The gameplay is very fun and energetic. It's not really complicated and can easily be done by a child. One thing I really liked about the game is that after you create your song, the game will mix all of the songs from that one Jamtenna into a remix which you can save as a .mp3 to your computer. You can create cover art while the game converts the remix into a .mp3. You aren't forced to save the songs, if you really don't like it.Conclusion: If you are hesitant on getting this game, buy it. It's cheap, fun, and will kill time if you need to. 9/10"
