76561198045326675,Recommended,297110,17279287,"Posted: 29 July, 2015",all,Zacnate,"This game is very simple and very fun to just mess around with.Being able to create simple beats and feel like you have control over how the song plays out is a cool idea and is brought out well considering. It is easy to go in and create a beat of your own with and you do not need to be a wiz with music making to do it well.  However this is where the negatives start to kick in.  In the game you go between 4-5 different instruments and create beats with essentially 4 different notes....and that's it really. There are bonus loops or instruments that can appear and give you the option of changing your current instrument with the new one or have the option of selecting new music in general.  Besides this there is no other way to make or alter music.  This is where the simplicity will be seen as a negative.  You are not able to fade music in or out, change the BPM, and there is no way to edit your samples the way YOU want after you create them.  The game will automatically edit the samples together which may make your song sound better or worse.  It is a shame that if you want to make advanced samples or create your own songs your out of luck really.  It took me 3 hours to go through the entire ""story"" section but I will say I had a lot of fun playing through it.  Even though you have limits to the kind of music you can make it is still a fun expereince that is worth that little bit of money it costs to play it.  People looking for an advanced music maker to make samples and great tracks would probably get nothing from this, but for players looking for a simple and fun music creation game to mess around and have fun with then there is nothing wrong with this game.  Did I forget to mention any song you finish you can save and export it to your music library on you computer to listen to whenever you want (even if the songs are just 1 minute long).  A lot of neat ideas in this game I just wish there would be options for more advanced options to give people freedom to create even more awesome tracks.    However because the game only costs a couple of dollars my negatives really are just minor.        Cosmic DJ get's a 7/10 From me.  ""It's good for what it provides you for a few dollars and gives you a fun time while providing cool and silly visuals that will put a smile on your face.""+Fun samples and good beat+Great Price+Easy to pick up and play+Able to Export your music converted automatically to MP3 to your computer library+/- Length of game is short but is reasonable considering price-Simplistic and does not offer any advanced means to create some real creative samples and tracks-some samples that you HAVE to use don't feel like they fit in the song your making-no way to select what instrument for when you create custom tracks"
