,Recommended,297110,22829945,"Posted: 6 May, 2016",all,Pizza Time,"Short, sweet, and to the point.This psychedelic trip of a game is very fun to mess around with. Overall there are about 6 'Areas' to play through and each one has 4 miniature 'stages' where you can play around with 5 different instruments/voxes. The backing tracks can only be changed a tiny bit through progression, the more stuff you put into a song the more options you might get to add into it even further.The story's funny to me personally, I rather liked the 'far out' voice of the narrator and the weird things that happen along the way. There's a charm to how simple this game is and honestly I couldn't stop playing once I picked it up.The soundtrack is awesome, especially since the player has quite a bit of influence over it, and there's even more charm to be found in a game that lets you export your little creations to a folder on your computer for later listenings (it's automatic, so don't expect a deep, in-depth music creator here).Even though the game is incredibly short (expect 2-4 hours depending on how much you want to screw around with the tracks) I found that it was definitely worth the price of admission. It doesn't hurt that I also got this game on sale for less than a dollar, but honestly even if it weren't on sale I'd still recommend it.It's only $3, just don't eat lunch for like, one day."
